  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Normal hearing listeners gain important everyday benefits from listening with two ears
      (bilateral hearing) compared to their baseline performance with hearing aids. Advantages of
      bilateral hearing include the ability to determine where sounds are coming from and the
      ability to hear sounds and understand speech in noisy environments. Based upon these
      advantages, this study will (1) evaluate the benefit of hearing with two Bionic Ear implants
      (one in each ear) and (2) compare HiResolution sound processing with conventional sound
      processing.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
